message.content:
cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with understanding and modeling teachers' teaching styles using natural language processing techniques.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a multi-task deep learning model to capture the correlations between cross-media features and teaching styles.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is relevant as the paper uses facial expressions and body motions as part of the cross-media features to model teaching styles.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper aims to improve teaching quality analysis, which is a human-computer interaction problem.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing feedback questionnaires to develop a Teaching Style Semantic Space (TSSS) and to model teaching styles.
